Program: Discovery
Title: Building Stonehenge
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwmv
Last Broadcast Date: 25 March 1996
A report on how Stonehenge may have been built earlier than had been at first thought. Also in the programme, tackling mosquito's with bacteria, tracking glacier and can science fully describe the world around us? Presenter: Ruth Linton.